Dear Both,

=20

Please find below summary of meeting I had with Dr Habiba and Dr Mohammed e=
arlier today. I have sent them this summary as well. Please let me know when=
 you have time to discuss.

=20

=20

Please find below a summary of our discussion.

=20
Data storage; Current situation=20
The BTC server is located in the BTC lab on main campus
Was purchased in 2017, and is likely out of support/maintenance.
We discussed the possiblity of moving to a more centralized model, where re=
sources are provided and managed centrally by research  computing.
It is connected as the storage for the output of the 4 sequencing machines =
at BTC.
The sequencing machines output data to the BTC when it is required, and thi=
s is generally when you have a specific project or  group of samples. As an =
estimate this is ~350GB at a time, every few weeks or when required
It is running out of storage, it has a total of 55TB and currently only 4TB=
 are free=20
Majority of space is consumed by intermediate files generated by the analys=
is pipelines
Dr Mohammed will explore removing some of the intermediate files, to see if=
 he can carry on with the analysis
I suggested that you create project and account on the HPC to get started o=
n your current analysis.=20
You will start with the standard allocation, 2TB project directory on the h=
igh speed filesystem, and 50Gb on home directory
If this proves inadequate, we will adjust as necessary
Storage purchased previously by Dr Habiba, was around 125 TB, of which ~80T=
B is currently utilized.=20
We discussed that the previous purchase was for hardware, which has a limit=
ed lifetime and needs to be refreshed periodically
I suggested that we try to move to purchasing storage as a service, where t=
he storage can persist over multiple hardware refreshes.
We will arrange another meeting to discuss how best to move forward with th=
e storage.=20
Dragen Server=20
Is comprised of specialized hardware and software for genomic analysis
You have purchased installation and support from local company, Purehealth.=
 This does not include Sysadmin support
Will need to mount/connect it to the 4 sequencers in BTC
Needs to be installed in a data center, as it is not suitable for a lab env=
ironment.
=20

I will arrange for a follow up meeting with Dr Mohammed early next week.

=20

Thanks,

Dureid

=20

=20

--=20

